= New Graduate Students

== Two Ph.D. positions are available at the department of Computer and Information Technology (CIT) at Purdue University starting in the Fall 2014. Applicants who are interested in conducting research in the areas of network data analytics, distributed systems/cloud computing, queueing theory or network simulation may contact Prof. Ioannis Papapanagiotou by email (see the following website for contact information): https://tech.purdue.edu/profile/ipapapan

The Universityœôòùs Admission Deadline is April 1st, but interested students are strongly advised to contact Prof. Papapanagiotou as soon as possible.

